To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Tennessee Public Records Act, I hereby request the following records:

Pursuant to the applicable Public Records Act / Freedom of Information laws, I respectfully request copies of any and all inmate disciplinary records, incident reports, rule violation reports, sanctions, or related documentation concerning Anna Henson with DOB 1/18/1996 during her period of incarceration from January 5, 2026 through January 24, 2026.

This request includes, but is not limited to:

Disciplinary charges or infractions

Incident or misconduct reports

Findings, determinations, or outcomes of any disciplinary proceedings

Sanctions imposed or recommended

Related logs or summaries referencing disciplinary matters

If no responsive records exist, please confirm that in writing.

If any portion of this request is denied or redacted, please identify the specific statutory basis for the denial or redaction and release any reasonably segregable non-exempt portions of the records.

Thank you for your assistance. Please feel free to contact me if you require clarification or additional information to process this request.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 7 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Kent Hoover, a citizen of Tennessee, in coordination with Frank Freeman.

title: Records to assess racism complainst against VMI

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Virginia Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

In regard to the statements made by Mr. Jeremiah Woos before the Education Committee of the Virginia General Assembly, I request the following records on former cadet Jeremiah Woods, VMI Class of ’27:

For any of these records, I agree that 1 Personal Identifiable Information will be properly redacted as may be required by law, so long as that redaction is properly noted.

1.	He stated: “I arrived at the VMI in the fall of 2023 on a full-ride scholarship.” – Provide the records for this scholarship, including sources of funding, any agreements, and the details on the scholarship itself 
2.	He stated: “I'm a black man, a former cadet leader, and a researcher of VMI's history.” 
a.	All records showing any leadership positions he held
b.	The period he held them.
c.	If removed from a leadership position, the reasons.
3.	He stated: “From the start, I faced racial targeting.”
a.	All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation. “A cadre member asked me whether my refusal to shave was an excuse because I am black. “
b.	All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation, “My white peers asked whether I'll be a field slave or a house slave.”
c.	All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation that his white peers “ asked if I would marry, kill, or have sex with George Floyd. When I said neither, they replied, they already killed George Floyd and no one cared, so it doesn't matter.”
d.	All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation. “When I spoke about the displacement of VMI's first black superintendent, threats escalated.”
e.	 All records from any complaint he filed through investigation and final adjudication of his allegation, as well as any social media posting to Jodel or other platforms, and responses from other cadets for his allegation. “One social media circulating among cadets. “All con. All con. President Trump has just passed the N-word, I'm going to effing kill you act. #Beadvised.” – I understand that Jodel is an anonymous application, but also understand cadets and VMI administrators have administrative access and that postings to social media are not protected under FERPA or the FOIA.
f.	Records of the RAT class trips to New Market from Mr. Woods Matriculation year to the present including any scripts, talking points or agendas for the trips and rosters for cadets attending in response to his allegation: “Each year, cadets are taken to the Battle of New Market and taught how Confederate troops who fought exemplify the highest level of the Brother RAT spirit while enslaved people who supported VMI are erased.” This is to include, without limitation, the specific record of the year(s) Mr. Woods attended the New Market event.
g.	Mr. Woods stated: “In 2021, VMI was required by law to establish a memorial and a scholarship. While VMI is the only institution of the five institutions named in the law, VMI has not yet established that memorial.” – Provide records of this requirement and the current status.
h.	Mr. Woods stated: “Jackson Hope board named after Stonewall Jackson.” – Provide the charter and results of the BOV review of monuments and namings report regarding the Jackson-Hope Medal.
i.	Mr. Woods stated on Social Media: “On 2025, I conducted historical research on enslaved African Americans who lived and worked at VMI, drawing from primary institutional sources. I presented this research publicly to a standing-room-only audience that included VMI officials and local elected leaders. My work demonstrated that enslaved people were essential to the daily operation of the institute, yet their lives remain largely absent from VMI’s Official commemorative landscape.” – It is my understanding this was a SURI project entitled “African Americans at VMI 1851 – 1865” under the VMI History Department. I request the record, including his research report with all underlying empirical information, his faculty and other advisors, reviews and drafts of his paper, correspondences regarding his paper and research, presentations, and attendance at the event he references.
j.	In his social media posts, he mentions building names after Confederate figures – I request a copy of the final monuments and memorials review report to the BOV and the BOV’s approval of said report.
k.	Mr. Woods identifies “confederate artillery” named “Matthew, Mark, Luke, and John” – records showing the confederate lineage of these weapons.
l.	Mr. Woods stated on social media: “Before ever speaking I met privately and repeatedly over the course of two years with Institute Officials across multiple administrations. I raised concerns about racial hostility, retaliation, and equity. These concerns were acknowledged, but meaningful change but did not follow.” – All records of these meetings especially with cadet leadership, Maj. Gen. Cedric Wins, Lt. Gen. Furness, the DEI/DOI/Inclusive excellence staffs or other Institute officials he met with.
m.	Mr. Wood stated “racist and threatening statements made by cadets on social media are real and documented.” – copies of these posts.
4.	Communications of any kind with Lt. Gen. David Furness, Maj. Gen. Cedric Wins, Col. Tinni Sen, Col. Keith Kline, or any member of the Title IX or DEO/DEI/Inclusive Excellence office from the date of his arrival at VMI to the present.

These allegations are a matter of great public interest and had significant impact of the General Assembly’s decision not move the bill to study if VMI should continue to receive state funding forward.  It is in the best interest of the public and VMI, especially its cadets, the facts of this matter are made public. To that end I request any fee for this FOIA be waived.

Further, in the past, VMI responded vaguely stating you could not locate some records.  In regard to the complaints Mr. Woods alleges he made should the search find no records I quest VMI clarify this by confirming “no record of any such complaint was found.”

It is in VMI’s best interest for the facts of this matter to be clear.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Tom Nash, a citizen of Virginia, in coordination with Anonymous.

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Untitled
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Please provide any documents responsive to request #EPA-R2-2016-008883, received on July 27, 2016.

The subject of the initial request is copied below:

PLEASE SEE ATTACHED LETTER. We respectfully request all materials related to the investigation of any equipment, buildings, sites, and/or locations in Bronx County, New York, in connection with any/all Legionnaires’ Disease outbreak(s), from January 1, 2014 to the present, including, but not limited to, all documents, records, correspondence, testing, sampling data, epidemiological data, research, laboratory results, reports, complaints, studies, photographs, memoranda, notices, warnings, fines, violations, citations, abatements of any cited conditions, inspection records, safety logs, inspections logs and reports, and witness statements including, but not limited to, all of the aforementioned materials related to the following: 1. South Bronx Legionnaires’ Disease Outbreak; 2. East Bronx Legionnaires’ Disease Outbreak; 3. Morris Park Legionnaires’ Disease Outbreak; 4. Opera House Hotel, at 436 East 149th Street, Bronx, New York 100455; 5. Citywide cooling towers investigation; 6. Legionella DNA fingerprinting and results, pulse field gel electrophoresis (PFGE) testing, sequenced based typing (SBT), and whole genome sequencing (WGs) of environmental samples and human isolates; 7. Any patient reporting of Legionnaires’ Disease and/or related illness; 8. Any testing performed at the New York Public Health Laboratory and New York Wadsworth Center Laboratory;

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Justine Streichenberger-Nicolas

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: Clinton County (IL) Dairy Subsidies - EXPEDITED REQUEST
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Dear FOIA Officer,

Please consider this a request under the the Federal Freedom of Information Act, 5 U.S.C. § 552.

Under the Act, I am requesting the 2024, 2023, 2022, 2021 and 2020 applications to receive subsidies under the programs: Dairy Margin Coverage (DMC), Milk Loss Program (MLP), Dairy Indemnity Payment Program (DIPP) for the following producers:
* Varel Dairy; Bartelso, Illinois.
* Thole AG; Aviston, Illinois.
* JB Timmermann Farms; Breese, Illinois.
* Four Beck Dairy; Bartleso, Illinois.
* C D & R Farms, Inc.; Breese, Illinois.
* Dall Dairy; Aviston, Illinois
* Glen Von Bokel Farms; Carlyle, Illinois
* Aaron Hilmes; Carlyle, Illinois
* Corey Hilmes; Breese, Illinois
* Arentsen Farms; Albers, Illinois

In order to help to determine my status to assess fees, you should know that I am reporter with Capitol News Illinois, and this request is made as part of news gathering and not for a commercial use. I request a waiver of all fees for this request. Disclosure of the requested information to me is in the public interest because it is likely to contribute significantly to public understanding of the operations or activities of the government and is not primarily in my commercial interest by exploring the federal supports to local dairy farmers. 

I hereby request expedited processing of this request pursuant to 5 U.S.C. § 552(a)(6)(E) because there is an urgency to inform the public concerning actual or alleged Federal Government activity, and I am a person primarily engaged in disseminating information,

Thank you for your consideration of this request.

Sincerely,

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

communications.subject: HUMAN RESOURCES DATA REQUEST :: R002057-012626
communications.communication:
Dear Cooper Quintin: 
Thank you for your interest in data from the Minnesota Department of Public Safety Human Resources division. Your request was received on 1/26/2026 and given the reference number R002057-012626 for tracking purposes. Your request is being processed in accordance with all applicable law and policy. 
You will receive an email to confirm the availability of the requested data and any costs when your request is processed.  You will be responsible for paying all costs associated with your request prior to any release of data. 
You can monitor the progress of your request and communicate with the Human Resources in the " My Request Center".  If you have any questions you may reply to this email.
Sincerely, 
Human Resources

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: ICE website changes
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Material removed from ice.gov from Jan. 20, 2025, to July 1, 2025, with any of the following keywords: trans, transgender, gender identity, intersex.

I additionally request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com, processed by a representative of the news media/press and is made in the process of news gathering and not for commercial usage.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Ileana Garnand

communications.subject: Freedom of Information Act Request: ICE trans care emails
communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Freedom of Information Act, I hereby request the following records:

Emails from all individuals who held the following positions or performed the duties of said positions with any of the following keywords. I request records from the timeframe of Jan. 20, 2025 to July 1, 2025.

Positions: Director, Deputy Director, Chief of Staff, Executive Associate Director of Enforcement and Removal Operations, Executive Associate Director of Homeland Security Investigations, Executive Associate Director of Management and Administration, Associate Director of Office of Professional Responsibility and Principal Legal Advisor.

Keywords: transgender, trans, biological sex, sex at birth, sex, gender, memorandum.

I additionally request that, if appropriate, fees be waived as I believe this request is in the public interest. The requested documents will be made available to the general public free of charge as part of the public information service at MuckRock.com, processed by a representative of the news media/press and is made in the process of news gathering and not for commercial usage.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 20 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,
